rules: Rule1: Whenever member1 can borrow publication1, publication1 is accessible.
Rule2: Either member1 can borrow publication1 or member1 can borrow publication2.
Rule3: Provided that publication1 is processed, it is not the case that publication1 is shelved.
Rule4: Under the condition that member1 is fined, if it is not the case that publication1 is not accessible implies publication1 is renewed, then publication1 is overdue.
Rule5: Member1 is fined or member1 is suspended.
Rule6: Either member1 is warned or, if member1 is suspended, then publication1 is not accessible implying publication1 is renewed leads to publication1 being overdue.
Rule7: If publication1 is returned, then publication1 is available.
Rule8: Provided that publication1 is reported by librarian1, then whenever publication1 is not returned, publication1 is missing.
Rule9: Publication1 is reported by librarian1 or publication1 is investigated by librarian1.
Rule10: If publication1 is resolved, then publication1 not returned implies publication1 is missing.
Rule11: Either publication1 is escalated or, provided that publication1 is investigated by librarian1, publication1 is resolved.
Rule12: If publication1 is cataloged, then publication1 is available.
Rule13: Provided that publication1 is classified, publication1 is available.
Rule14: Whenever publication1 is labeled, publication1 is cataloged.
Rule15: If publication1 is indexed, then publication1 is classified.
Rule16: Under the condition that publication1 is accessioned, either publication1 is labeled or publication1 is indexed.
Rule17: If publication1 is referenced, then publication1 is available.
Rule18: Provided that publication1 is cited, publication1 is referenced.
Rule19: If publication1 is available, then member1 can borrow publication2 implying publication1 is accessible.
Rule20: Provided that publication1 is reserved for member2, publication1 is checked out.
Rule21: Either publication1 is reserved for member2 or publication1 is reserved for member3.
Rule22: If publication1 is reserved for member3, then publication1 is available.
Rule23: Whenever publication1 is checked out, publication1 is available.
Rule24: Publication1 is lost or publication1 is damaged or publication1 is accessible.
Rule25: If publication1 is repaired, then publication1 is shelved.
Rule26: Provided that publication1 is repaired, publication1 is processed.
Rule27: Either publication1 is repaired or publication1 is not lost.
Rule28: If it is not the case that publication1 reserved for member2 implies publication1 is cited, then publication1 is withdrawn.
Rule29: Provided that publication1 reserved for member2 does not imply publication1 is cited, publication1 is not withdrawn.
Rule30: If publication1 not being accessible leads to publication1 being renewed, then publication1 is not overdue.
facts: Fact2: It is not the case that publication1 is renewed.
